MR. KONDA SRINIVAS, presented with complaints of angina.
ECG showed SR, QS with ST elevation in leads V1-V4, upright T wave in V1-V6.
Bedside Echo revealed RWMA in anterior wall, distal IVS & Apex, LVEF 38%, moderate LV dysfunction, grade I diastolic dysfunction,
He was diagnosed to have ACS - Evolved AWMI, and was treated with LMWH, dual antiplatelet drugs, nitrates, and statins.
On 03.11.2021, coronary angioram was done that revealed CAD, single vessel disease (proximal LAD), and was given Heparin
infusion and Tirofiban infusion for 48 hours
On 05.11.2021. successful PTCA/stent to proximal LAD was done with good result with TIMI III flow. Procedure was uneventful.
There were no major peri/post procedural complications. Detailed procedure report enclosed
He improved symptomatically and was discharged at request in a stable condition with an advise to continue following
# Monitor blood sugars & blood pressure regularly and record it and maintain BP less than 140/90 mmHg.
# Advised to follow strict diabetic, low salt, low fat diet as advised.
# Do not lie down flat for 2-3 hours after food intake.
# Advised to do Yoga/Physiotherapy regularly (Breathing & Palateal exercises, Resistance leg exercises/strength training exercises).
